 Working with K8S and Docker for the Offline module :

 step 1) step the folder structure / image creation:
    - create the job_cleanser.py
    - define the docker for that
    - build docker :  docker build -t job-nlp-classifier:latest .
    - login the docker hub from terminal with : docker login
    - tag the image on docker hub with the command :docker tag job-nlp-classifier:latest codebyte17/jobs-recommendations:latest
    - push the image - docker push codebyte17/jobs-recommendations:offline-latest
  Now we have the image on docker hub registry , which is ready for deployment on K8S

  step 2) Define the jobs.yml file
    - kind: job (it is job not deployment , means run only once and then finished from K8S)
    - how to start on K8S :  kubectl apply -f jobs.yml

  step 3) Some commands for kubectl to explore the pods and jobs
    - see all pods : kubectl get pods
    - see all jobs : kubectl get jobs
    - check the logs of pod : kubectl logs  pod job-nlp-classifier2-fr8d6
    - describe / know the pods details : kubectl describe pod job-nlp-classifier2-fr8d6




 step last) copy the save file into local machine for further exploration with command
    - kubectl cp pvc-debug:/mnt/jobs/processed_jobs.csv ./processed_jobs.csv